Lady Zhen - Wikipedia






















 






Lady Zhen

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
  (Redirected from Zhen Luo)

					Jump to:					navigation, 					search

This article is about the wife of Cao Pi of Wei of the Three Kingdoms. For the empress, the wife of Cao Fang of Wei of the Three Kingdoms, see Empress Zhen (Cao Fang). For the noble consort of the Xianfeng Emperor, see Empress Dowager Ci'an.


Lady Zhen



A Qing dynasty illustration of Lady Zhen



Noble lady of Cao Wei


Born
(183-01-26)26 January 183[a]


Died
4 August 221(221-08-04) (aged 38)[b][c]


Names


Traditional Chinese
甄夫人 / 甄氏


Simplified Chinese
甄夫人 / 甄氏


Pinyin
Zhēn Fūrén / Zhēn Shì


Wade–Giles
Chen Fu-jen / Chen Shih


Posthumous name
Empress Wenzhao (Chinese: 文昭皇后; pinyin: Wénzhāo Huánghòu; Wade–Giles: Wen-chao Huang-hou)


Other names


Empress Zhen (Chinese: 甄后; pinyin: Zhēn Hòu; Wade–Giles: Chen Hou)
Zhen Luo (Chinese: 甄洛; pinyin: Zhēn Luò; Wade–Giles: Chen Lo)
Zhen Fu (Chinese: 甄宓; pinyin: Zhēn Fú; Wade–Giles: Chen Fu)
Zhen Ji (Chinese: 甄姬; pinyin: Zhēn Jī; Wade–Giles: Chen Chi; literally: "Consort Zhen")




This is a Chinese name; the family name is Zhen.
Lady Zhen (26 January 183[1] – 4 August 221[2][3]), personal name unknown, was the first wife of Cao Pi, the first ruler of the state of Cao Wei in the Three Kingdoms period. In 226, she was posthumously honoured as Empress Wenzhao when her son, Cao Rui, succeeded Cao Pi as the emperor of Wei.



Contents


1 Early life
2 Marriages to Yuan Xi and Cao Pi
3 As Cao Pi's wife
4 Death

4.1 Alternative account of Lady Zhen's death
4.2 Alternative theories on Lady Zhen's death


5 Posthumous honours
6 Reliability of alternative historical sources on Lady Zhen's life
