Other names


Empress Zhen (Chinese: 甄后; pinyin: Zhēn Hòu; Wade–Giles: Chen Hou)
Zhen Luo (Chinese: 甄洛; pinyin: Zhēn Luò; Wade–Giles: Chen Lo)
Zhen Fu (Chinese: 甄宓; pinyin: Zhēn Fú; Wade–Giles: Chen Fu)
Zhen Ji (Chinese: 甄姬; pinyin: Zhēn Jī; Wade–Giles: Chen Chi; literally: "Consort Zhen")




This is a Chinese name; the family name is Zhen.
Lady Zhen (26 January 183[1] – 4 August 221[2][3]), personal name unknown, was the first wife of Cao Pi, the first ruler of the state of Cao Wei in the Three Kingdoms period. In 226, she was posthumously honoured as Empress Wenzhao when her son, Cao Rui, succeeded Cao Pi as the emperor of Wei.



